text: Eudonia deltophora is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by Edward Meyrick in 1884. This species is endemic to New Zealand. The wingspan is 21–23 mm. The forewings are light greyish-ochreous, irrorated with whitish. The hindwings are grey-whitish. Adults have been recorded on wing in January. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1884 Category:Scopariinae Category:Moths of New Zealand Category:Taxa named by Edward Meyrick Category:Endemic fauna of New Zealand
